rt futures’ in which expert groups and organizations decline in power and status as their prevalence proliferates to a stage where they become ubiquitous in neoliberal regimes. Finally, the book presents an alternative reflexive model of expert authority and governance that is grounded in the ‘dynamics of contestation and trust’ and stands in direct contrast to the orthodox, rational model.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aExperte. 4aExpertenautorität. 4aFunktionale Autorität. 4aMacht. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aControl.  aExpert authority.  aExperts.  aPower.1 aReed, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL0 cEPUBz97831107349730 cprintz978311073905340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311073491140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110734911423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110734911/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  a978-3-11-131926-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSLb2023